06/02/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Netherlands and France have asked for a monitoring mechanism for the visa-free regime for BiH and Albania, Srna news agency reported on Friday (February 4th). 
In a letter sent to the European Commission (EC), the two countries said the time has come to introduce such a mechanism and sanctions should be imposed in case of abuses. 
Citizens of BiH and Albania have been free to travel without visas in the Schengen Zone since December 15th. 
(Srna, Nezavisne Novine, Dnevni Avaz - 04/02/11)
